org.wso2.carbon.identity.openidconnect

Interface OpenIDConnectClaimFilter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    OpenIDConnectClaimFilterImpl

    public interface OpenIDConnectClaimFilter
    This extension can be used to control how claims are filtered based on requested claims in id_token and user info response.

    • Method Detail

      • getClaimsFilteredByOIDCScopes

        Map<String,Object> getClaimsFilteredByOIDCScopes(Map<String,Object> userClaims,
                                                 String[] requestedScopes,
                                                 String clientId,
                                                 String spTenantDomain)
        Filter user claims based on OIDC Scopes defined.

        Each OIDC Scope defined has a set of permitted claims. First we consider the requested scopes and aggregate the allowed claims for each requested scope if they are defined OIDC Scopes. Then we filter the user claims which belong to the aggregated allowed claims.

        Parameters:
        spTenantDomain - Tenant domain of the service provider to which the OAuth app belongs to.
        requestedScopes - Request scopes in the OIDC request.
        userClaims - Retrieved claim values of the authenticated user.
        Returns:
        Claim Map after filtering user claims based on defined scopes.

      • getClaimsFilteredByOIDCScopes

        List<String> getClaimsFilteredByOIDCScopes(Set<String> requestedScopes,
                                           String spTenantDomain)
        Filter list of claims based on OIDC Scopes requested.

        Each OIDC Scope defined has a set of permitted claims. We consider the requested scopes and aggregate the allowed claims for each requested scope if they are defined as OIDC Scopes.

        Parameters:
        requestedScopes - Request scopes in the OIDC request.
        spTenantDomain - Tenant domain of the service provider to which the OAuth app belongs to.
        Returns:
        List of claims based on the defined scopes.
